{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"stats-hub","type":"text","text":"## 📊 The Global Treatment Gap\n\n- **1+ billion** people live with mental health conditions (WHO 2024)\n- **Low-income countries**: <10% receive care\n- **High-income countries**: ~50-75% treatment gap\n- **Nigeria**: >90% treatment gap\n- **US**: 29.5M adults received NO treatment (48%)\n- **Global median** mental health workers: 13 per 100,000\n- **Mental health budgets**: Only 2% of total health budgets globally\n- **Depression & anxiety cost**: $1 trillion/year in lost productivity","x":-800,"y":-440,"width":350,"height":520},
		{"id":"global-disparities-2025","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12531183/","x":-1250,"y":250,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"public-stigma-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12835938/","x":-400,"y":500,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"self-stigma-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12835938/","x":0,"y":500,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"structural-stigma-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8786211/","x":400,"y":500,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"stigma-medical","type":"text","text":"### ⚕️ Stigma Reduces Treatment Effectiveness\n\nStigma doesn't just prevent seeking help-it reduces adherence and medical effectiveness once treatment begins.","x":-800,"y":200,"width":320,"height":200},
		{"id":"stigma-medical-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12228425/","x":-800,"y":500,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"south-asian","type":"text","text":"### 🛕 South Asian Context: 'Izzat' (Family Honor)\n\n- Mental health = weakness, lack of resilience\n- Prioritize family reputation over individual needs\n- Suppress issues to avoid bringing shame\n- Intergenerational trauma from partition/war/displacement\n- Parents dismiss mental health support: 'therapy is for other people'","x":-400,"y":980,"width":350,"height":370},
		{"id":"south-asian-paper","type":"link","url":"https://behavioralhealthnews.org/therapy-is-for-other-people-why-many-south-asian-parents-dismiss-mental-health-support/","x":-400,"y":1450,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"south-asian-blog","type":"link","url":"https://southasiantherapists.org/blog/how-cultural-affect-mental-health-for-south-asians/","x":-850,"y":1200,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"lmic-barriers","type":"text","text":"### 💰 Low & Middle Income Countries\n\n- Budget share <1% for mental health\n- Psychiatrist density <1 per 100,000\n- Treatment gaps >75%\n- Cultural stigma: mental problems hidden within families\n- Fear of ostracization\n- Community-based interventions vital but underfunded","x":0,"y":1030,"width":350,"height":320},
		{"id":"lmic-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4355984/","x":0,"y":1450,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"lmic-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12939-024-02106-6","x":450,"y":1200,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"cultural-adapt-paper","type":"link","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41746-021-00498-1","x":900,"y":1450,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"sexual-main","type":"text","text":"## 🔒 SEXUAL HEALTH & EMBARRASSMENT\n\nSexual health issues are among the most stigmatized and least discussed-creating massive untreated populations.","x":0,"y":1920,"width":400,"height":180},
		{"id":"sexual-stigma","type":"text","text":"### 😳 Sexual Health Stigma\n\n- Shame & guilt surrounding sexual dysfunction\n- Fear of judgment prevents seeking help\n- Low libido, sexual dysfunction, intimacy anxiety\n- Cultural taboos make discussion impossible\n- 'Education and open communication are essential in breaking down shame' - Dr. Patti Britton","x":-400,"y":1980,"width":350,"height":370},
		{"id":"sex-therapy","type":"text","text":"### 💬 Why Anonymous Sex Therapy Works\n\n- CBT techniques challenge negative thought patterns\n- Sex therapy explores identity in safe, judgment-free space\n- Anonymity removes fear of social exposure\n- Digital platforms allow gradual disclosure\n- Critical for cultures where premarital/consensual issues are taboo","x":0,"y":2200,"width":350,"height":360},
		{"id":"literacy-main","type":"text","text":"## 🧠 MENTAL HEALTH LITERACY BARRIERS\n\nPeople can't seek help for problems they don't recognize. Poor literacy = poor recognition = no treatment.","x":0,"y":2920,"width":400,"height":180},
		{"id":"literacy-barriers","type":"text","text":"### 📚 Key Literacy Barriers\n\n- **Poor symptom recognition**: Don't know they have a condition\n- **Lack of awareness**: Don't know where to seek help (35% of students)\n- **Low perceived need**: 34% don't view their condition as serious\n- **Self-reliance preference**: 41% prefer to manage alone\n- **Youth especially affected**: stigma + embarrassment + poor literacy","x":-400,"y":2980,"width":350,"height":370},
		{"id":"literacy-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3022639/","x":-400,"y":3450,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"literacy-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12447698/","x":0,"y":3200,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"literacy-paper-3","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12541994/","x":450,"y":3200,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"trust-main","type":"text","text":"## 🔐 TRUST, PRIVACY & THERAPIST RELATIONSHIP\n\nWithout trust, therapy fails. Digital platforms must actively build trust through verification, security, and professional standards.","x":0,"y":3920,"width":400,"height":180},
		{"id":"trust-factors","type":"text","text":"### 🔑 What Builds Trust in Digital Therapy?\n\n1. **Therapist education verified** on platform\n2. **Secure payment process** (fraud protection)\n3. **Platform as guarantor** of quality\n4. **Recommendations/reviews** from others\n5. **Convenient format** & temporal independence\n6. **Technical reliability**\n\n*Trust = f(Specialist, Platform, Payment, Education)*","x":-400,"y":3940,"width":350,"height":440},
		{"id":"privacy-concerns","type":"text","text":"### 🛡️ Privacy Concerns\n\n- **28%** cite privacy concerns as barrier\n- Fear of data breaches & exposure\n- Confidentiality breaches in small communities\n- Fear of academic/employment records being affected\n- Anonymous platforms eliminate this risk","x":0,"y":4200,"width":350,"height":300},
		{"id":"teletherapy-paper-1","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12772077/","x":1400,"y":350,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"teletherapy-paper-2","type":"link","url":"https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2024.07.30.24311208v1.full","x":1850,"y":100,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"teletherapy-paper-3","type":"link","url":"https://behavioralhealthnews.org/telehealth-versus-face-to-face-therapy-for-treating-anxiety-evidence-based-considerations-for-clinicians/","x":1850,"y":550,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"anonymous-therapy","type":"text","text":"### 🎭 Anonymous Therapy Research\n\n- **Anonymous online CBT** for social anxiety: Trial underway (NCT06465589) with 452 participants\n- Anonymous tools process NO personal data → removes privacy barrier\n- Users may have **preference** for anonymous versions\n- Anonymity reduces stigma-related dropout\n- **Key insight**: Anonymity + evidence-based treatment = accessible care without identity risk","x":1400,"y":780,"width":400,"height":370},
		{"id":"anonymous-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12631092/","x":1400,"y":1250,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"digital-meta","type":"text","text":"### 📈 Digital Mental Health: Meta-Analysis Results\n\n**For cancer patients (proxy for general population):**\n- **Anxiety reduction**: SMD = -0.38 (significant)\n- **Depression reduction**: SMD = -0.35 (significant)\n- **Psychological distress**: SMD = -0.40 (significant)\n- **Most effective modalities**: mHealth, telehealth, social media-based\n- **Duration**: Both <8 weeks and ≥8 weeks effective\n- **Conclusion**: DHIs significantly improve mental health outcomes","x":1400,"y":1800,"width":400,"height":460},
		{"id":"digital-youth","type":"text","text":"### 👶 Digital Interventions for Youth\n\n- Significant impact on reducing anxiety, stress, depression\n- Improves mental health literacy & well-being\n- Interactive tools & gamification improve adherence\n- **BUT**: Need parental involvement, cultural sensitivity, and professional acceptance\n- Digital platforms ideal for adolescents who fear stigma","x":1850,"y":1650,"width":400,"height":330},
		{"id":"digital-youth-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11941436/","x":1850,"y":2100,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"value-prop","type":"text","text":"## 🌳 Proposition\n\n### What the Research Proves We Need:\n\n1. **Anonymity** → Eliminates stigma, privacy & cultural barriers\n2. **Licensed verification** → Builds trust (education visible)\n3. **Video + voice calls** → Proven as effective as in-person\n4. **Accessible 24/7** → Solves time & geographic barriers\n5. **Cultural matching** → Essential for LMIC & diaspora populations\n6. **Sexual health specialization** → Addresses highest-embarrassment domain\n7. **Self-reliant tools** → Appeals to 41% who prefer self-management\n8. **Transparent pricing** → Solves cost barrier (28%)\n\n### Market Validation:\n- **1B+** untreated globally\n- **Telehealth** = clinically equivalent\n- **Anonymous** = removes #1 barrier (stigma)\n- **Youth (18-25)** = highest need + most tech-comfortable","x":1400,"y":3000,"width":450,"height":700},
		{"id":"central-problem","type":"text","text":"# 🌳 The Therapy Gap\n## Why 1 Billion+ People Avoid Mental Health Care\n\n*A research-backed knowledge base on barriers to therapy and the case for anonymous, licensed digital therapy.*","x":160,"y":-440,"width":500,"height":200},
		{"id":"stigma-main","type":"text","text":"## 🚫 STIGMA: The #1 Barrier\n\nStigma operates at 3 interconnected levels, creating complex barriers to care. ~450M people affected worldwide.","x":-120,"y":-160,"width":400,"height":160},
		{"id":"public-stigma","type":"text","text":"### 👥 Public Stigma\n\nNegative attitudes & discriminatory behaviors by society. Fear of being labeled, ostracized, judged. Leads to social exclusion and hiding symptoms.","x":-400,"y":170,"width":320,"height":180},
		{"id":"structural-stigma","type":"text","text":"### 🏛️ Structural Stigma\n\nDiscriminatory policies & practices within institutions (healthcare, workplaces). Institutional barriers that limit opportunities and access to care.","x":440,"y":110,"width":320,"height":180},
		{"id":"college-main","type":"text","text":"## 🎓 COLLEGE STUDENTS: A High-Need, Low-Help Population\n\nMeta-analysis of 62 studies reveals critical barriers for young adults.","x":-1280,"y":820,"width":400,"height":160},
		{"id":"college-barriers","type":"text","text":"### 📋 Top Barriers (Meta-Analysis)%\n\n| Barrier | Prevalence |\n|---------|-----------|\n| Self-management preference | **41%** |\n| Lack of time | **41%** |\n| Don't know where to go | **35%** |\n| Low perceived need | **34%** |\n| Perceived cost | **28%** |\n| Privacy concerns | **28%** |\n| Stigma | **28%** |\n| Prefer informal help | **26%** |\n| Difficult to access | **23%** |\n| Fear of unwanted treatment | **22%** |\n| Cultural insensitivity | **8%** |\n\n*Only 28% actively seek formal help*","x":-1280,"y":1025,"width":380,"height":515},
		{"id":"college-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12447698/","x":-1250,"y":1720,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"sexual-stigma-paper","type":"link","url":"https://headroom.co.za/overcoming-stigma-in-sexual-health/","x":-720,"y":2580,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"cultural-sexual-paper","type":"link","url":"https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/09540260701278903","x":450,"y":2700,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"privacy-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC12447698/","x":0,"y":4700,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"trust-paper","type":"link","url":"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11311150/","x":-425,"y":4700,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"digital-meta-paper","type":"link","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41746-025-02266-x","x":900,"y":2220,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"solution-main","type":"text","text":"# ✅ THE SOLUTION: Model\n## Anonymous, Licensed, Digital Therapy\n\n*Research strongly supports the effectiveness of teletherapy and anonymous digital interventions.*","x":1350,"y":-560,"width":450,"height":200},
		{"id":"teletherapy-effective","type":"text","text":"### 📱 Teletherapy = In-Person Effectiveness\n\n- **Meta-analysis of 35 RCTs** (4,827 participants): Telehealth is NON-INFERIOR to face-to-face for depression & anxiety\n- **SMD = -0.03** for depression (no significant difference)\n- **SMD = -0.06** for anxiety (no significant difference)\n- **PTSD**: Telehealth actually showed SMALL ADVANTAGE (SMD = -0.21)\n- Therapeutic alliance ratings are COMPARABLE\n- Patient satisfaction is HIGH","x":1400,"y":-240,"width":400,"height":390},
		{"id":"cultural-main","type":"text","text":"## 🌍 CULTURAL BARRIERS\n\nMental health is not culturally neutral. Family honor, collectivism, and traditional beliefs create powerful barriers.","x":540,"y":965,"width":400,"height":140},
		{"id":"cultural-adapt","type":"text","text":"### 🔧 Cultural Adaptation is Essential\n\nInternet/mobile interventions need 17-component cultural adaptation for LMICs/migrants. Without adaptation: lower effectiveness & adherence. Key: language, daily life illustrations, collectivism values, local risk factors.","x":950,"y":1080,"width":350,"height":270},
		{"id":"who-atlas-2024","type":"link","url":"https://www.who.int/news/item/02-09-2025-over-a-billion-people-living-with-mental-health-conditions-services-require-urgent-scale-up","x":-1300,"y":-400,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"self-stigma","type":"text","text":"### 😔 Self-Stigma\n\nInternalizing negative beliefs → shame & loss of self-efficacy. Diminishes self-esteem. Creates profound reluctance toward help-seeking.","x":0,"y":120,"width":320,"height":180}
	],
